8. CONCLUSION
-------------

This long-context alignment experiment demonstrates that the failure of language models to retain instructions and facts over extended sequences is not an inevitable physical limitation of the transformer architecture. Rather, it is a representational failure of flat prompting methods.

By encapsulating systems invariants within a structured, dual-axis XML schema, you establish stable coordinates in the model's active global workspace (the J-space). 

This allows even compact models running locally on developer hardware to evaluate and enforce complex systems constraints implicitly during the forward pass—delivering safe, zero-latency, and highly-aligned execution without relying on explicit, written reasoning traces.

